{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/simple-click/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"718bcc12-f638-5311-8f12-12dbd7d42395","html":"<p>cli tools are super handy and easy to add to your python libraries to supercharge them. Even if your library is not a cli tool there are a number of things that a cli can do to your library.</p>\n<h1>Example Ideas</h1>\n<p>Things a cli can do to enhance your library.</p>\n<p>üÜö print version\nüï∂ print readme\nüìù print changelog\nüìÉ print config\n‚úè change config\nüë©‚Äçüéì run a tutorial\nüèó scaffold a project with cookiecutter</p>\n<h1>üñ± <a href=\"https://click.palletsprojects.com/\">Click</a></h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://click.palletsprojects.com/\">Click</a> is the most popular python cli tool framework for python. There are others, some old, some new comers that make take the crown. For now <a href=\"https://click.palletsprojects.com/\">Click</a> is the gold standard if you want to make a powerful cli quickly. If you are dependency conscious and dont need a lot of tooling, use <a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/argparse.html\">argparse</a>.</p>\n<h1>Project Structure</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">.\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ setup.py\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ simple_click\n    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cli.py\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ __init__.py</code></pre></div>\n<h1>‚ùØ cli.py</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">    <span class=\"token comment\"># simple_click/cli.py</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> click\n\n    __version__ <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"1.0.0\"</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token decorator annotation punctuation\">@click<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>group</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">cli</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n       <span class=\"token keyword\">pass</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token decorator annotation punctuation\">@cli<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>command</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">version</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n        <span class=\"token triple-quoted-string string\">\"\"\"prints project version\"\"\"</span>\n        click<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>echo<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>__version__<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> __name__ <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token string\">'__main__'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n        cli<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h1>‚ú® <strong>init</strong>.py</h1>\n<p>For our simple<em>click library <code class=\"language-text\">__init__.py__</code> can be left empty. It is here purely to signify that simple</em>click is a library. It is likely that you will import other modules here that need to reside at the top level of your library api, your cli does not need to be at the top of of your api.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">    <span class=\"token comment\"># __init__.py</span></code></pre></div>\n<h1>üö™ Entry Points</h1>\n<p>Entry points are the magic that make python cli tools available as their own command without having python before it or the file extension.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">    <span class=\"token comment\"># setup.py</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> setuptools <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> setup<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> find_packages\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># this is the ü•© meat of this snippet</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># simple_click is the command name</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># = simple_click is the library name</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># .cli is the cli.py file</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># :cli is the cli function</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">#</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># the second item is a shorthand alias to the main command</span>\n\n    entry_points <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n       <span class=\"token string\">\"simple_click = simple_click.cli:cli\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n       <span class=\"token string\">\"scli         = simple_click.cli:cli\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n\n\n    setup<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n        name<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'simple_click'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        version<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'1.0.0'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        url<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'https://github.com/mypackage.git'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        packages<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>find_packages<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        entry_points<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token string\">\"console_scripts\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> entry_points<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h1>üï∂ See it in action</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--RiG3kZsy--/c_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_66%2Cw_880/https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/4zrhvj5yjzyk63np91g9.gif\"><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--RiG3kZsy--/c_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_66%2Cw_880/https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/4zrhvj5yjzyk63np91g9.gif\" alt=\"See it in action\" title=\"See it in action\"></a></p>\n<h1>üì¢ Discuss</h1>\n<p>What do You wish more python libraries included in their cli?  <a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=@_waylonwalker%20More%20libraries%20should%20...%0A%0Awaylonwalker.com/b/scli\">Tweet it @_waylonwalker</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=@_waylonwalker%20More%20libraries%20should%20...%0A%0Awaylonwalker.com/b/scli\" alt=\"Tweet it @_waylonwalker\"></p>","fields":{"slug":"/blog/simple-click/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-01-29T06:00:00.000Z","devto_url":"","devto_id":"","title":"simple click","description":"Add helpful cli to your python libraries... All of them!","path":"simple_click","twitter_cover":{"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/waylonwalkerv2/waylonwalkerv2/static/2020-02-02 09-40-45_Start.png","childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":726,"height":379,"src":"/static/575086d7a2e7efdc84b3968017c3286e/721a8/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png","srcSet":"/static/575086d7a2e7efdc84b3968017c3286e/721a8/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png 1x"}}},"cover":{"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/waylonwalkerv2/waylonwalkerv2/static/2020-02-02 09-40-45_Start.png","childImageSharp":{"fixe